headline: PG&E Commits $50 Million to Expand Bill Relief for Customers with Past-Due Energy Bills
summary: Pacific Gas and Electric Company (PG&E) is committing $50 million to new and existing financial assistance programs to support eligible customers with paying past-due energy bills. These programs include PG&E's new Match My Payment Program and the existing PG&E Relief for Energy Assistance through Community Help (REACH) program.
